-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

---:[ Requirements

Perl
Net::RawIP
NetPacket
Net::PcapUtils
Pcap library


---:[ Disclaimer

THIS PROJECT WAS DEVELOPED FOR TESTING AND DEMONSTRATION PURPOSE ONLY! 
THE AUTHORS DONT FEEL RESPONSIBLE FOR ILLEGAL ABUSE OF THIS PIECE OF 
SOFTWARE AND WE ADVICE YOU TO USE IT LEGALLY AND DO NOT BREAK THE LAW!


---:[ Description

Hijackd is a daemon for automatically hijacking plain protocols.
Please note: If you dont specify an infiltrate string hijackd will use a
string which adds a user to /etc/passwd and /etc/shadow. The user is called
hacker and the password is also hacker.


---:[ Installation

Get the required Perl modules from CPAN [ http://www.cpan.org ] and install 
them. Download libcap from www.tcpdump.org and compile it.


---:[ Usage

Run ./hijackd --help to get help.

